            <h3 class="title-v2 text-left">Food Should be a Conscious Choice</h3>
            <h3 class="title-v5 text-left">“How we eat food is as important as what we eat” - Sadhguru</h3>
            <p class="text-justify">
                We have been taught to eat healthy since our childhood, yet we give in to taste and have food with low nutritional value. Vegetables, fruits, whole grains, healthy proteins, water instead of sugary beverages are common recommendations for intake. However, we must always focus on the diet quality. It translates to the notion that the type of carbohydrates in the diet is more important than the amount of carbohydrates in the diet. <br>
                <br>
                Various people tie their food choices to religious beliefs. But as a sensible human being, you should not leave it on your religion to decide your choices for food. Food is the fuel that drives you. Considering the good and bad of it, you must figure out yourself, which type of food works the best for you. To make your food intake more effective, here are some facts you should be conscious of. <br><br>

                <ul>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check color-golden"></i>  Food should be consumed within 1.5 hours of cooking or getting off the stove.</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check color-golden"></i>   A fruit is fully digested within 1.5 to 3 hours. </li>
                    <li> <i class="fa fa-check color-golden"></i> Cooked vegetables take 12-15 hours for digestion.</li>
                    <li> <i class="fa fa-check color-golden"></i> Cooked cereals take 24 to 30 hours to digest.</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check color-golden"></i> Raw meat takes 72 hours to digest.</li>
                    <li> <i class="fa fa-check color-golden"></i> Cooked meat takes 48 to 52 hours to digest.</li>
                </ul><br>

                The longer your food remains in your body higher are the possibilities of bacterial birth within your system. So, what to eat, how much to eat and when to eat should always be a conscious choice.
            </p>
        </div>
