<div class="container space-100">
    <div class="col-md-7 center-block float-none space-padding-tb-100">
        <h3 class="title-v2 text-center">What Ayurveda Says about your Body Type</h3>
        <h3 class="title-v5 text-center">“The same dimension that made Krishna or Jesus who they were, exists within you and people around you. It just needs your attention to blossom.” – Sadhguru</h3>
        <p class="text-center">One of the most significant components of Indian Ancient Wisdom – Ayurveda explains that the human body is made up of five elements: Air, Space, Fire, Water and Earth. These elements in their biological form are known as Doshas namely Vatta, Pitta, and Kapha. These 3 elements create unique physical, mental, and emotional characteristics among a human being.  </p>
    </div>
    <div class="clearfix"></div>
    <div class="col-md-4 wow slideInLeft" data-wow-duration="2s" data-wow-delay="0.4s">
        <h3 class="title-v2 text-center">Vatta</h3>
        <img src="~/assets/images/vatta.jpg" alt="Vatta" class="img-responsive">
        <p class="text-justify space-padding-30">Vata relates to movement in the body (blood circulation, digestion, activity in the nervous system and brain). Vata body types usually have small body frames and can be overactive, indecisive, nervous, concerned and fearful. According to Ayurveda, Vatta personalities are generally slim and can eat whatever they want without putting on weight. Vata skin is Normal to Dry while hair trends to be prone to dryness and frizziness, hence needs to be conditioned and nourished regularly.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4 wow zoomIn" data-wow-duration="2s" data-wow-delay="0.5s">
        <h3 class="title-v2 text-center">Pitta</h3>
        <img src="~/assets/images/pitta.jpg" alt="Pitta" class="img-responsive">
        <p class="text-justify space-padding-30">Pitta controls chemical transformations related to energy, digestion and metabolism. Pitta dispositions are often impatient and easily angered or irritated. Because they are aggravated by heat, they should avoid heat-inducing food, hot weather and alcohol. Pitta dispositions need to be cooled. Pitta skin is generally Normal with the forehead, nose and chin generally oily and the rest is dry. They generally have lustrous and manageable hair, which is prone to premature greying.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4 wow slideInRight" data-wow-duration="2s" data-wow-delay="0.5s">
        <h3 class="title-v2 text-center">Kapha</h3>
        <img src="~/assets/images/kapha.jpg" alt="Kapha" class="img-responsive">
        <p class="text-justify space-padding-30">Kapha relates to fluid balance and the physical structure of the body (fat, tissues, muscles). Kapha is calm and relaxed and can gain weight easily. When not in balance, their metabolism slows, resulting in sluggishness, lethargy and depression. Kapha is prone to putting on weight even with a regular diet. Kapha skin is generally Normal to Oily, hair tends to be thick and lustrous, and however, it is prone to oiliness which needs to be balanced..</p>
    </div>
    <div class="clearfix"></div>
    <div class="col-md-7 float-none center-block"><p class="text-center">A sustainable wellness practice would require you to determine the most dominant Dosha in your constitution and reshape your lifestyle to create a balance among these elements. </p></div>
</div>
